festival.introText:
Just A Tribute Festival 23 is taking over Apps Court Farm in Walton-on-Thames (near Kingston in London) to bring you one epic and memorable Tribute event. Join them to pay tribute to some of the most influential rock bands of all time, performed by some of the world’s best Tribute Bands, bringing you as close to the authentic experience as possible.

This year they are paying homage to Nirvana - Bon Jovi - Foo Fighters - Red Hot Chili Peppers - Pearl Jam - Slash & Myles Kennedy - Green Day and Paramore!

Rock out as a family and let the kids play in the funzone, with inflatables, rides and games. Or get some you time, grab your festival buddies and spend the day rocking out to great music with great people.

IT’S GONNA ROCK!

reviews.title: Review of Just A Tribute Festival 22
reviews.body: Had a fantastic day. So much talent for such a small price. unfortunately there were too few people there for such a large venue which meant it lost a bit I'd atmosphere to start with, which was not great for the first couple of bands. However, we were first there and last to leave. Really hope it was just down to nervousness following Covid, and hopefully it'll be busier next year - felt bad for organisers as they must have lost money. Given that, I've already booked my hotel for next year, PLEASE bring back "Hybrid Theory", all bands were fab but they stood out as exceptional ðð¤

reviews.title: Review of Just A Tribute Festival 22
reviews.body:
I absolutely loved it. Just a shame some of the tributes were on so early that we missed them. Over eight hours was just too long to spend in a field late-September!

It would possibly be preferable to have slightly shorter sets with shorter intervals (not that they were long) and just cram this event into five or so hours.

The early 9.30pm finish was a good idea so people could get home.

reviews.title: Review of Just A Tribute Festival 22
reviews.body: I thought the event on the whole was fabulous. Great music, great atmosphere, friendly team. What I was disappointed with was the No re-entry policy when a simple band would have solved that issue. We came the night before from York and camped over so we could go back and forth to the tent like most others weâve been to, for jackets and the like so we donât have to carry everything for the whole day. Would recommend those locally but wouldnât travel that far again for it. Great experience once though.

faqs.question: When is Just a Tribute Festival 2023?
faqs.answer: Just a Tribute Festival takes place on Saturday 30th September 2023.

faqs.question: is there camping available at just a tribute festival 2022?
faqs.answer:
Camping is available directly from Apps Court Farm

Camp at Apps Court Farm for Just A Tribute22! Included in the camping tickets is the use of their brand new toilet and shower facility. 

All camping tickets are charged for the two night stay (Friday – Sunday)

 

PLEASE NOTE THAT CAMPING DOES NOT INCLUDE ENTRANCE TO JUST A TRIBUTE FESTIVAL!!

 

Click here for more info - https://www.justatribute.co.uk/just-a-tribute-festival-camping/

faqs.question: disabled access information
faqs.answer: for information on accessibility please contact dan.carden81@gmail.com

faqs.question: How much is a ticket to Just a tribute festival
faqs.answer:
Adult tickets for just a tribute festival start from £30 +bf

Teen tickets for just a tribute festival start from £15 +bf

kids U14 go free however a ticket is still needed to be purchased.

faqs.question: Where is Just a Tribute Festival?
faqs.answer: Just a Tribute Festival is located at Apps Court Farm in Walton-on-Thames. the full address is Hurst Rd, Walton-on-Thames KT12 2EG

faqs.question: Do you need a ticket for parking
faqs.answer:
Yes, you need a parking ticket for just a tribute festival and these start from £5 +bf

 

Car and coach parking is permitted only in the designated areas and with a valid parking ticket bought in advance. Vehicles parked elsewhere may be removed.

faqs.question: Are there any age restrictions for Just a Tribute Festival?
faqs.answer:
All ages are allowed to attend the festival.

No unaccompanied under 18s are allowed on site. Under 18s must be accompanied by a responsible adult aged over 21 years old who has purchased a valid ticket.

 

 The sale and consumption of alcohol is strictly prohibited to persons under the age of 18 years. Just A Tribute Festival and its concessions employ the ’Challenge 25’ scheme. If you are lucky enough to look under 25 you will be asked to prove that you are over 18 years old when you buy alcohol or tobacco. The only acceptable forms of identification are either an ID card bearing the PASS hologram that is endorsed by the PASS scheme or failing this a valid passport or driving licence. For more information about the PASS scheme please visit http://www.pass-scheme.org.uk

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

 

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

reviewsDisplayFour.title: Review of Just A Tribute Festival 22
reviewsDisplayFour.body: This was a great event, 7year olds first festival/live music event and it was perfect, great atmosphere, staff were helpful and friendly. Facilities and site were clean.  Line up was a really good mix and the bands were of a high standard.  Food price was a little high, but bar and sweets were good value.  Water was a little hard to find, especially as the tickets surgetsed you could fill empty bottles.  It was a shame you could not get in and out of the car, especially for a family event.  Roll on next year....
